# HackerPhone

Idea:

- Wireless Router w/ USB, running [`OpenWRT`](http://openwrt.org)
- [USB Audio "Phone"](#nolink) -- really just an USB audio card with mic and speaker in form of a fone
- = `HackerPhone`

# Hardware

- TP-Link WR703N or better
- cheap USB handset

# Software

- Asterisk can be used as client, but should be too bloated
- there is [`baresip`](https://forum.openwrt.org/viewtopic.php?id=31129) - but no info on howto use
- [Sofia-SIP](http://sofia-sip.sourceforge.net) -- lib used by FreeSWITCH
- [Linphone](http://www.linphone.org) - läuft super auf linux, mac und iOS. gab [patches für openwrt](https://dev.openwrt.org/ticket/1679)

